## Remarks  
 The <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlLink> control allows programmatic access to the HTML `link` element on the server. The <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlLink> control can be used to programmatically specify a cascading style sheet (CSS) reference in a Web page.  



## Examples  
 The following code example demonstrates using the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlLink> control to programmatically add a style sheet to a Web page.  

 <!-- TODO: review snippet reference [!code-csharp[System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlLink#1](~/samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_WebNet/System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlLink/CS/htmllinkcs.aspx#1)]  -->
 <!-- TODO: review snippet reference [!code-vb[System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlLink#1](~/samples/snippets/visualbasic/VS_Snippets_WebNet/System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlLink/VB/htmllinkvb.aspx#1)]  -->  

 To run the preceding code example, you need a cascading style sheet (CSS) named `Stylesheet.css`, containing the following code, saved in the same directory as your Web site.  

```vb  
body {  
  padding-left: 11em;  
  font-family:  Verdana, "Times New Roman",  
        Times, serif;  
  color: blue;  
  background-color: silver }  
h1 {  
  font-family: Helvetica, Geneva, Arial,  
        SunSans-Regular, sans-serif;   
  color: purple }  
```  

```csharp  
body {  
  padding-left: 11em;  
  font-family:  Verdana, "Times New Roman",  
        Times, serif;  
  color: blue;  
  background-color: silver }  
h1 {  
  font-family: Helvetica, Geneva, Arial,  
        SunSans-Regular, sans-serif;   
  color: purple }  
```
